cs.CY, cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 

1. cs.CY (Computers and Society): This paper discusses the use of technology in modeling medical processes, which falls under the domain of computers and society. 

2. cs.DB (Databases): The proposed approach involves modeling various kinds of medical processes, which requires the use of databases to store and manage the data. 

3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses how the proposed approach can be used to deal with an interplay of all the processes a patient is subject to, which involves human-computer interaction. 

4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The artifact-centric process modeling technique mentioned in the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence to model complex processes. 

5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The proposed approach involves the development of a software system to model medical processes, which falls under the domain of software engineering.
